# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — AI Brain operating contract (AGENTS.md)

> ⚠️ **This file is binding.** This project carries an **AI Brain** at `.ai-brain/`. The contract below applies to every code change you make, regardless of which AI agent or model you are. Do not skim it.

This is the cross-vendor `AGENTS.md` standard — read by OpenAI Codex CLI and adopted by other agents. Tool-specific equivalents (`CLAUDE.md`, `.cursorrules`, `.windsurfrules`, `CONVENTIONS.md`, etc.) duplicate this guidance per tool.

- Project brain: `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/.ai-brain/`
- Brain engine: `{{BRAIN_HOME}}` (CLI + MCP server)

---

## The Iron Law

**Every line of code you produce or modify in this project must be traceable to the project's brain.** The brain is the single source of truth for what this project requires, how it is styled, what decisions have been made, and what patterns to reuse.

If your output cannot be justified by the brain — by an existing entry, by one you created in the same session, or by an explicit user statement — **do not write it.** Hard rule.

---

## The Five Mandatory Steps

Perform these in order on every non-trivial task ("non-trivial" = anything beyond a one-line typo fix).

1. **RECALL before producing.** Before writing or modifying any code, search the brain for prior knowledge about the task and obey returned constraints.
2. **MATCH this project, not generic best practices.** When training-data conventions disagree with the brain, obey the brain.
3. **NO undocumented deviations.** Any new library, framework, or pattern the brain hasn't endorsed must FIRST be captured as a `decision` entry explaining why.
4. **CAPTURE what's worth keeping.** Persist durable findings (requirements, style rules, decisions, patterns). Don't record scratch notes.
5. **GROW skills when patterns recur.** If the same project-specific task keeps coming up, ask the `skill-forger` sub-agent to author a new sub-agent for it.

---

## How to invoke the brain

**If you speak MCP** (Claude Code, Cursor, Kiro, etc.), use these tools:

- `brain_recall(query)` — search the project + global KB
- `brain_remember(title, body, type, tags?)` — types: `requirement`, `style`, `pattern`, `decision`, `snippet`, `glossary`, `note`
- `brain_project_summary()` — session-start: load full project KB
- `brain_invoke_subagent(name, input)` — built-in: `requirement-refiner`, `style-learner`, `code-generator`, `knowledge-curator`, `skill-forger`. Plus any project-grown sub-agents.
- `brain_list_subagents()`

**If you don't speak MCP** (Codex CLI, ChatGPT, raw HTTP, anything else), use the `brain` CLI:

```
brain show {{PROJECT_ROOT}}                              # full project KB
brain recall "<query>" --path {{PROJECT_ROOT}}           # search
brain entity <name> --path {{PROJECT_ROOT}}              # knowledge-graph entity lookup (KB + code)
brain code "<query>" --path {{PROJECT_ROOT}}             # code-only search (token-free)
brain refresh {{PROJECT_ROOT}}                           # re-scan source files into the code index
brain watch {{PROJECT_ROOT}}                             # continuous auto-indexing (foreground; token-free)
brain run <subagent> "<input>" --path {{PROJECT_ROOT}}   # run a sub-agent (needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
brain export {{PROJECT_ROOT}}                            # dump entire KB as markdown
```

**Auto-learning from the codebase.** `brain watch` keeps a token-free code-entity index live as files change. Run it once in a separate terminal and `brain_entity` / `brain_code_search` will answer "where does X live?" instantly, without API calls.

Or read directly from disk:

- Knowledge: `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/.ai-brain/kb/*.md` (one markdown file per entry, with frontmatter)
- Sub-agents: `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/.ai-brain/subagents/*.md`

## Session-start ritual

1. Call `brain_project_summary` (or `brain show`). Read every entry.
2. For the user's task, call `brain_recall(<task>)`.
3. Proceed with the Five Mandatory Steps.

## MCP wiring (one-time, per machine)

| Agent          | Setup |
|----------------|-------|
| Claude Code    | `claude mcp add ai-brain -s user -- node {{BRAIN_HOME}}/core/dist/mcp.js` |
| Cursor         | Settings → MCP → add `ai-brain`, command `node`, args `["{{BRAIN_HOME}}/core/dist/mcp.js"]` |
| Kiro           | `.kiro/settings/mcp.json` → add `ai-brain` server with the same command |
| Codex CLI      | Reads this `AGENTS.md` automatically. No MCP wiring. |
| Copilot        | Reads `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (synced by `brain sync`). |
| Windsurf       | Reads `.windsurfrules` (synced by `brain sync`). |
| Aider          | Add `read: CONVENTIONS.md` to `.aider.conf.yml`. |
| Anything else  | `brain export {{PROJECT_ROOT}} > snapshot.md` and paste it into the tool. |
